{{Infobox language family |name=East Strickland |region=[[New Guinea]] |familycolor=Papuan |fam1=[[Papuan Gulf languages|Papuan Gulf]] ? |fam2=Strickland |glotto=east2433 |glottorefname=East Strickland |map=East Strickland languages.svg |mapcaption=Map: The East Strickland languages of New Guinea {{legend|#FF5E5F|The East Strickland languages}} {{legend|#7BB5B6|Other Trans–New Guinea languages}} {{legend|#D9D9D9|Other Papuan languages}} {{legend|#E09D00|Austronesian languages}} {{legend|white|Uninhabited}} }}
The '''East Strickland languages''' are a [[language family|family]] of [[Trans–New Guinea languages]] in the classification of [[Malcolm Ross (linguist)|Malcolm Ross]]. The six languages, *[[Fembe language|Fembe]] (Agala) *[[Odoodee language|Odoodee]] (Tomu) *[[Konai language|Konai]] *Central: [[Gobasi language|Gobasi]] (Nomad), [[Kubo language|Kubo]], [[Samo language (New Guinea)|Samo]] (Daba) are clearly related.
Gobasi, Odoodee and Samo, but especially Gobasi, are also known as "Nomad".
Pronouns are:
:{| ! !!sg!!du!!pl |- !1 |*na, *ã||*o-li, *a-la||*oi |- !2 |*nõ||*nĩ-le||*nĩ |- !3 |*yõ||*i-le||*yã, *di |}
