{{multiple image|caption_align=center|header_align=center| align = right| direction = horrizontal| width = 175| header = Swakopmunder Buchhandlung emergency money| image1 = SWA-6-Swakopmunder Buchhandlung-10 Pfennig (1916).jpg| alt1 = | caption1 = 1916 Ten Pfennig| image2 = SWA-15a-Swakopmunder Buchhandlung-Two Mark (1916).jpg| alt2 = | caption2  = 1916 Two Mark }}
The '''[[South-West Africa]]n [[mark (money)|mark]]''' was a temporary currency issued between 1916 after the withdrawal of the [[German South-West Africa]]n [[German South West African Mark|mark]], and prior to the introduction of the [[South African pound]] in 1918.

A number of notes were denominated in South West African marks and [[pfennig]], especially by the [[Swakopmund Bookshop]] that issued 10, 25, 50 Pfennig, and 1, 2, and 3 mark notes.{{sfn|Cuhaj|2010|p=548}}
